          {
            "commit": "c6ab1fcc056778b18f685ec591ce27907e887617",
            "subject": "LU-4381 lov: to not hold sub locks at initialization"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Andreas Dilger",
          "email": "andreas.dilger@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-03-05 18:59:30.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-03-10 23:51:15.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-4708 ldiskfs: do not copy NUL terminator from direntry",
        "message": "LU-4708 ldiskfs: do not copy NUL terminator from direntry\n\nDo not try to copy a NUL terminator from the source dirent if there\nis no dir_data for that record.  This can happen with 1.x filesystems\nthat do not have a dirdata field in the dirent to store the FID.\n\nThe target buffer is expected to be NUL terminated, and this is\nhandled by using kzalloc() to allocate it and zero out the buffer,\nbut the source buffer may not have a trailing NUL byte if it is a\nmultiple of 4 bytes in length.\n\nIf the dirent is aligned at the end of the directory block/page this\ncan cause an oops by accessing beyond the end of the page, or will\notherwise copy a garbage byte to the target buffer.\n\nSigned-off-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Iab52f916d7571b3d2587255280c72a52c60399c9\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/9510\nTested-by: Jenkins\nReviewed-by: Niu Yawei <yawei.niu@intel.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
